===Noun===
'''acre''' (''plural'' '''acres''')
#A unit of surface area (''symbol'' a. ''or'' ac.) equal to 43,560 [[square foot|square feet]], used for measuring geographical features such as land and bodies of water.  If measured as a square it would be approximately 208.71 feet on each side. <!--This is the English statute acre. That of the United States is the same. The Scotch acre was about 1.26 of the English, and the Irish  1.62 of the English. Most commonly used to measure land (or things on land, such as the floor of a building, or sports fields), but can also be used to measure the surface area of bodies of water.-->
#(''in plural, colloquial'') A large amount (of area).
#:''I like my new house - there's '''acres''' of space!''

